    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h3 id="AeroCMS-v0-0-1-SQLi-update-categories-sql-injection"><a href="#AeroCMS-v0-0-1-SQLi-update-categories-sql-injection" class="headerlink" title="AeroCMS-v0.0.1-SQLi update_categories_sql_injection"></a>AeroCMS-v0.0.1-SQLi update_categories_sql_injection</h3><h4 id="Step-to-Reproduct"><a href="#Step-to-Reproduct" class="headerlink" title="Step to Reproduct"></a>Step to Reproduct</h4><p>Login to admin panel -&gt; <code>Categories</code> -&gt; Edit.The <code>edit</code> parameter from the AeroCMS-v0.0.1 CMS system appears to be vulnerable to SQL injection attacks. The malicious user can dump-steal the database, from this CMS system and he can use it for very malicious purposes.</p><h4 id="Exploit"><a href="#Exploit" class="headerlink" title="Exploit"></a>Exploit</h4><p><img src="/2018/09/06/AeroCMS-v0.0.1-SQLi%20update_categories_sql_injection/image-20221114180739852.png"></p><p>Query out the current user</p><p><img src="/2018/09/06/AeroCMS-v0.0.1-SQLi%20update_categories_sql_injection/image-20221114162919152.png"></p><h4 id="Vulnerable-Code"><a href="#Vulnerable-Code" class="headerlink" title="Vulnerable Code"></a>Vulnerable Code</h4><figure class="highlight apache"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs apache"><span class="hljs-attribute">AeroCMS</span>-<span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">1</span>\admin\categories.php<br><span class="hljs-attribute">AeroCMS</span>-<span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">0</span>.<span class="hljs-number">1</span>\admin\includes\update_categories.php<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>The edit parameter is passed in the GET mode and brought into the mysql_query() function without filtering</p><p><img src="/2018/09/06/AeroCMS-v0.0.1-SQLi%20update_categories_sql_injection/image-20221114163303682.png"